      "charStart": 3615,
      "factId": "hz.web.717a540e2d0d98a1.fact.3",
      "kind": "bullet",
      "text": "This approach allows teams to tap into their creative brains and build deeper trust while effectively learning and testing what really works.</p> </div> <div class=\"membership-restricted-banner style-light\"> <h3>RESTRICTED CONTENT</h3> <h4>Subscribe to EJ+ to gain access to our full library of Evergreen Content</h4> <p> <a href=\"/evergreen-journal-plus-benefits\" class=\"border-width-0 cursor-init custom-link btn custom-button-white btn-color-xsdn btn-flat\">Subscribe</a><br /> <a href=\"/login\" class=\"login-link-restricted\">Login here if you are a subscriber</a> </div> <p>The post <a href=\"https://www.tugboatinstitute.com/uncertainty-friend-or-foe/\">Uncertainty: Friend or Foe?</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.tugboatinstitute.com\">Tugboat Institute</a>.</p> ]]></description> <content:encoded><![CDATA[<style> .membership-restricted-banner { background-color: #40AE38; color: #fff; padding: 40px 20px; text-align: center; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 60px; } .membership-restricted-banner h3 { font-weight: 900; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #fff; } .membership-restricted-banner h4 { font-weight: 500; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 20px; color: #fff; } .membership-restricted-banner a { color: #000 !important; } .membership-restricted-banner a.login-link-restricted { color: #fff !important; display: block; margin-top: 20px; } .membership-restricted-preview { position: relative; } .membership-restricted-preview::after { content: \"\"; display: block; position: absolute; bottom: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100px; background: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0), rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)); } .live-sessions-single + .row-container { display: none !important; } </style> <div class=\"membership-restricted-preview\"><p>In this <a href=\"https://www.tugboatinstitute.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Tugboat Institute®</a> talk, Amy Bonsall draws on her experience at IDEO to argue that uncertainty is an ess