    "bullets": [
      "<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?><rss version=\"2.0\" xmlns:content=\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\" xmlns:wfw=\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\" xmlns:dc=\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\" xmlns:atom=\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\" xmlns:sy=\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\" xmlns:slash=\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\" > <channel> <title>Tugboat Institute</title> <atom:link href=\"https://www.tugboatinstitute.com/feed/\" rel=\"self\" type=\"application/rss+xml\" /> <link>https://www.tugboatinstitute.com/</link> <description>Tugboat Institute is a community for CEOs and Presidents of private, profitable, and enduring companies.</description> <lastBuildDate>Mon, 30 Mar 2026 23:06:18 +0000</lastBuildDate> <language>en-US</language> <sy:updatePeriod> hourly </sy:updatePeriod> <sy:updateFrequency> 1 </sy:updateFrequency> <generator>https://wordpress.org/?v=6.9.1</generator> <image> <url>https://www.tugboatinstitute.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/cropped-favicon.ico-1-32x32.png</url> <title>Tugboat Institute</title> <link>https://www.tugboatinstitute.com/</link> <width>32</width> <height>32</height> </image> <item> <title>Uncertainty: Friend or Foe?</title> <link>https://www.tugboatinstitute.com/uncertainty-friend-or-foe/</link> <dc:creator><![CDATA[Anna O'Neill]]></dc:creator> <pubDate>Tue, 31 Mar 2026 06:00:10 +0000</pubDate> <category><![CDATA[Video]]></category> <category><![CDATA[Evergreen Journal]]></category> <category><![CDATA[People First]]></category> <category><![CDATA[pragmatic innovation]]></category> <category><![CDATA[Leadership]]></category> <category><![CDATA[creativity in business]]></category> <category><![CDATA[light actions]]></category> <category><![CDATA[uncertainty]]></category> <guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://www.tugboatinstitute.com/?p=10431</guid> <description><![CDATA[<style> .membership-restricted-banner { background-color: #40AE38; color: #fff; padding: 40px 20px; text-align: center; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 60px; } .membership-restricted-banner h3 { font-weight: 900; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #fff; } .membership-restricted-banner h4 { font-weight: 500; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 20px; color: #fff; } .membership-restricted-banner a { color: #000 !important; } .membership-restricted-banner a.login-link-restricted { color: #fff !important; display: block; margin-top: 20px; } .membership-restricted-preview { position: relative; } .membership-restricted-preview::after { content: \"\"; display: block; position: absolute; bottom: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100px; background: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0), rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)); } .live-sessions-single + .row-container { display: none !important; } </style> <div class=\"membership-restricted-preview\"> <p>In this <a href=\"https://www.tugboatinstitute.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Tugboat Institute®</a> talk, Amy Bonsall draws on her experience at IDEO to argue that uncertainty is an essential ingredient for creative growth rather than a flaw to be rushed through.",
      "She cautions against the use of the word “experiments” that can carry heavy expectations—rigid goals that trigger stress and shut down neural pathways—and instead advocates for the language of “light actions.”</p> <p>By shifting from heavy experiments to small, curiosity-driven actions, leaders can foster a mindset of Pragmatic Innovation where the primary goal is learning rather than gaining immediate revenues.",
      "This approach allows teams to tap into their creative brains and build deeper trust while effectively learning and testing what really works.</p> </div> <div class=\"membership-restricted-banner style-light\"> <h3>RESTRICTED CONTENT</h3> <h4>Subscribe to EJ+ to gain access to our full library of Evergreen Content</h4> <p> <a href=\"/evergreen-journal-plus-benefits\" class=\"border-width-0 cursor-init custom-link btn custom-button-white btn-color-xsdn btn-flat\">Subscribe</a><br /> <a href=\"/login\" class=\"login-link-restricted\">Login here if you are a subscriber</a> </div> <p>The post <a href=\"https://www.tugboatinstitute.com/uncertainty-friend-or-foe/\">Uncertainty: Friend or Foe?</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.tugboatinstitute.com\">Tugboat Institute</a>.</p> ]]></description> <content:encoded><![CDATA[<style> .membership-restricted-banner { background-color: #40AE38; color: #fff; padding: 40px 20px; text-align: center; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 60px; } .membership-restricted-banner h3 { font-weight: 900; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #fff; } .membership-restricted-banner h4 { font-weight: 500; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 20px; color: #fff; } .membership-restricted-banner a { color: #000 !important; } .membership-restricted-banner a.login-link-restricted { color: #fff !important; display: block; margin-top: 20px; } .membership-restricted-preview { position: relative; } .membership-restricted-preview::after { content: \"\"; display: block; position: absolute; bottom: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100px; background: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0), rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)); } .live-sessions-single + .row-container { display: none !important; } </style> <div class=\"membership-restricted-preview\"><p>In this <a href=\"https://www.tugboatinstitute.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Tugboat Institute®</a> talk, Amy Bonsall draws on her experience at IDEO to argue that uncertainty is an essential ingredient for creative growth rather than a flaw to be rushed through."
